Diagnosis
. Female with yellowish-white antennal clava (
Fig. 14
); hind leg with coxa, trochanter and major part of femur white (
Fig. 14
), fore wing infumate with median one-third darker brown (
Fig. 14
); male with strongly pedunculate funiculars (
Fig. 20
); both sexes with head and mesosoma dark brown to black (
Figs 13
, 
19
), pronotal collar without a carina along anterior margin (
Figs 13
, 
19
), with two pairs of long and strong setae on midlobe of mesoscutum (
Figs 13
, 
19
), and with sublateral grooves on mesoscutellum ±straight in lateral part, joining in posterior part (
Figs 13
, 
19
).

